verbose_text: Overexpression of Kif1A-GFP (XREF_FIG H and 3I; XREF_SUPPLEMENTARY) did indeed increase the vesicle velocity (XREF_FIG J), mobile vesicle percentage (XREF_FIG K), and pause frequency (XREF_FIG L) of S135E and S135A vesicles to similar levels in WT neurons (where the S135E vesicle pause frequency was even higher than that of S135A) but not in Syt4 knockout neurons.
